raw_text: ANANDAKUMAR,​ LUCIAN KUSHWANT – Beloved son of the late S. Anandakumar (Former Associate Editor,​ Sunday Observer),​ loving son of Chulani Wickramasinghe,​ brother of Yashan (Australia) and Narmada (UK),​ expired. Cremation will take place at 6 p.m. at the Kotikawatte Cemetery on Wednesday (20). Remains will be at No. 235,​ Sri Sumana Mawatha,​ Kelanimlla,​ Angoda,​ until 5.00 p.m. on Wednesday (20). 0774984594.059554

DHARMAPALA – SENARATH – Loving husband of Irene,​ father of Devika and Dr Arinda (Prof. University of Peradeniya),​ son-in-law of Sunil Karunaratne (NDB) and Dr Sayuri (Teaching Hospital,​ Peradeniya),​ grandfather of Devina & Divyani. Cortege leaves residence,​ Dharmasoka Mawatha,​ Aruppola,​ Kandy at 3.00 p.m. on Wednesday,​ the 20th September 2023 for General Cemetery,​ Mahaiyawa (Anglican Section).059722

EYABALAN – MUTTIAH – Beloved husband of Ratnavathy (Ratna,​ nee Nathaniel). Son of late Paramu William Muttiah and late Sugirtham (Kanapathipillai),​ son-in-law of late Robert Navaratnam Nathaniel and Florence Suhirtham (nee Walton),​ loving brother of Jeyaveeran and Vathani,​ late Jeyatheeran and Dawn Anuba,​ Jeyayogam and Kingsley George,​ brother-in-law of the late Vetharajan Nathaniel and Gnanes,​ the late Sathiyavathy and the late Perinpanayagam,​ Gnanasoundari and Stephen Selvadurai,​ loving father of Dushan and Jeyanthi,​ Pretheeva and Julian,​ affectionate grandfather to Benjamin,​ Sonya,​ Nathan,​ Rebekha and Miriam,​ Esther,​ Ruth,​ Samuel. Safe in the Arms of Jesus,​ died peacefully on the evening of September 16,​ 2023 surrounded by family. Funeral on Thursday,​ September 21st at 1.00 p.m. at Beechwood Cemetery,​ Ottawa. Following an hour of private family viewing,​ there will be a time of public visitation from 11 a.m. prior to the service.059581
